<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>After closing at 5940 last night, the FTSE 100 index got off to a positive start this morning, and was up around 0.85 per cent in early trading. </p>

<p>Melrose Industries has confirmed it plans to make a 'significant' number of job cuts at its GKN Aerospace business.</p>

<p>FTSE 100-listed Melrose suffered a £560million loss in the first half of the year, which is considerably more than the £131million loss seen at the same point a year ago.</p>

<p>Melrose said consultations with affected staff and unions were already 'well underway', with the board adding that GKN Aerspace looked set to enjoy a 'better performance' next year.  </p>

<p>Ofgem has fined SSE over £2million for a 2016 blunder which is likely to have pushed up wholesale electricity costs.</p>

<p>Ofgem said it would send a 'strong message' to energy producers that they must share timely information with others on the market.</p>

<p>British travel firm Dart Group has said it will continue to add further capacity for the rest of the summer.</p>

<p>It said it will change its name to Jet2 plc, and named Stephen Heapy as its chief executive officer.</p>

<p> </p>
